---
// Donate — D · Manifesto
// Paper-mute band. A single long-form paragraph with roman-numeral
// anchors, ending on two CTAs. Matches the Manifesto landing's voice.
import { SPONSORS_URL, BMC_URL } from "../../lib/config";
---

<section id="f-donate" class="sec">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">§ An honest ask</div>
    <h2 class="display">
      Open source is a <span class="accent">gift</span>. <br class="md-only" />
      Gifts need <span class="accent">keepers</span>.
    </h2>

    <div class="body">
      <p>
        CLUB is given away under Apache 2.0 because software that governs
        how your team publishes code should never be rented. But giving it
        away doesn't mean nobody paid for it. Servers have bills, releases
        take time, issues need answers, and the gap between "works for me"
        and "works for your team at 2 AM" is where the hours go.
      </p>
      <p>
        If your company depends on CLUB, consider a recurring sponsorship.
        It's the difference between a project that survives on weekends and
        one that ships on a schedule you can plan around. If you're an
        individual who just wants to say thanks, a coffee works too.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="cta-row">
      <a href={SPONSORS_URL} class="btn btn-primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Sponsor on GitHub
        <span class="btn-arrow">→</span>
      </a>
      <a href={BMC_URL} class="btn btn-ghost" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Buy me a coffee
      </a>
    </div>

    <ul class="tenets">
      <li>
        <span class="n mono">I.</span>
        <div>
          <strong>No perks, no unlocks.</strong>
          <span class="mute">Sponsorship funds maintenance, not features. Everyone gets the full product.</span>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="n mono">II.</span>
        <div>
          <strong>No rug pulls.</strong>
          <span class="mute">Apache 2.0, forever. Fork it tomorrow if anything changes.</span>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="n mono">III.</span>
        <div>
          <strong>No strings attached.</strong>
          <span class="mute">Cancel anytime, any amount. Zero obligation if it stops making sense.</span>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .sec { padding: 6rem 0; background: var(--color-bg); color: var(--color-ink); }
  .wrap { max-width: 64rem; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 2.5rem; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .wrap { padding: 0 1.25rem; } }

  .eyebrow { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-stamp); }
  .display {
    font-family: var(--font-sans); font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(2.1rem, 3.5vw + 0.5rem, 3.5rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.028em; line-height: 1.08;
    margin: 1rem 0 0; max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .md-only { display: none; } @media (min-width: 768px) { .md-only { display: block; } }
  .accent { color: var(--color-stamp); }

  .body {
    margin-top: 2.5rem; max-width: 42rem;
    font-size: 1.08rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-mute);
  }
  .body p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .cta-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.75rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; }

  .tenets {
    list-style: none; padding: 0;
    margin: 3rem 0 0;
    display: grid; gap: 0.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-top: 2rem;
  }
  .tenets li {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 2.25rem 1fr; gap: 0.75rem;
    align-items: baseline;
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
  }
  .tenets .n { color: var(--color-stamp); font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .tenets strong { color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 640; font-size: 0.98rem; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-right: 0.5rem; }
  .tenets .mute { color: var(--color-mute); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.55; }
  .mono { font-family: var(--font-mono); }
</style>
